1	/*
2	GPT-2 Transformer Neural Net trained in raw CUDA
3	Non-trivial notes to be aware of:
4	
5	We are being clever in the backward pass to conserve memory.
6	In particular, all parameters use a += in the backward pass, so we
7	can later do gradient accumulation. But all activations have = instead of +=
8	because these are faster (just read, no write). This is okay for all activations
9	except for those in the residual stream, where the gradients have to add. We make
10	sure that those parts work out ok and that we do a += as necessary. E.g.,
11	the layernorms are connected to the residuals so we += in layernorm backward.
12	*/
13	
